Is it possible to put colors to WATCHFMT? Here is what I have achieved by
far:

WATCH_COLOR_MY_NUMBER_DATE="%{"$'\e[32;40m'"%}"

WATCH_COLOR_RESET="%{"$'\e[39;49;00m'"%}"

export WATCHFMT="[%B${WATCH_COLOR_MY_NUMBER_DATE}${MY_NUMBER_DATE} ${MY_TIME}${WATCH_COLOR_RESET}%b] %B%n%b has %a %B%l%b from %B%M%b"

juhtolv@heresy:/home/juhtolv % log
[%{%}2001-07-28 11:23:15%{%}] juhtolv has logged on pts/0 from :0
[%{%}2001-07-28 11:24:06%{%}] juhtolv has logged on pts/2 from :0:S.0
[%{%}2001-07-28 11:24:56%{%}] juhtolv has logged on pts/3 from :0
[%{%}2001-07-28 11:40:18%{%}] juhtolv has logged on pts/4 from :0:S.1
[%{%}2001-07-28 14:02:22%{%}] juhtolv has logged on pts/6 from :0
juhtolv@heresy:/home/juhtolv % 

I can see green color in right places, but those curly braces and
percent signs are really annoying. So, what I should do?

Originally it was like this:

export WATCHFMT="[%B${MY_NUMBER_DATE} ${MY_TIME}%b] %B%n%b has %a %B%l%b from %B%M%b"

